[REGALE THEM WITH A STORY]

>When you arrive at the entrance to the woods, the clouds roll in.
>The once-warm daylight cools to a smooth indigo.
>The rain begins to fall.  Not a downpour, but a light drizzle.  The kind of rain that taps on the leaves of the trees, but never makes it to the forest floor.
