>Shadowy, faceless individuals walk through the forest.  As they aimlessly walk, they eventually seem to fade away into nothingness, never breaking their stride.
>As they vanish, the forest steadily grows larger and more convoluted in layout, straight paths twisting into veritable Celtic knots.
>The canopy grows thicker, and the sunlight fades away...
>You snap back to reality, and break away from Sumner.
>You don't quite understand it, but you don't like the implications of that vision.

[LEAVE]

>You are growing extremely uncomfortable with this situation.
>"Well, uh... I've enjoyed talking with you, but I should really get going."
>Sumner sprouts a branch tipped with a large leaf.  This branch blows in an invisible wind, almost making it seem that the deer is waving at you.
>"Yeah, uh... nice t0 meet ya, but we're 0utta here."
>GOODBYE, SUMNER
>The three of you carefully retreat, keeping all eyes on the deer head.
>Despite the sinister aura you now pick up on, there is no apparent barrier between you and your exit.
>In fact, the three of you manage to get away from Summer with no hitches.
>You sense the mysterious entity staring at you, even from a distance.
>Soon, you find yourselves in the midst of the woods, back in the clearing you know you passed through earlier.
>You can see the path you entered the woods from, and you can even see your car.
>Phew.  You half expected the woods to... shuffle around, or something like that.

[GO HOME]

>With immense relief, you climb into your car.  Pyr3 and Percy hop in as well, and you speed off to your house.
>"That... was, uh... interesting.  Thank you both for having my back.  I don't know what I would've done without you."
>"N0 pr0blem.  I was ready t0 turn him int0 rubble if he tried anything."
>I WOULD HAVE GOTTEN YOU OUT.
>"Thanks, you two."
>The two ladies smile warmly, and gaze back at the forest as you drive away.
>"...what a creep he was, huh?  But... he didn't even try t0 st0p us."
>VERY STRANGE.  HE SEEMS FRIENDLY
>Hm.
>Eventually, you make it home.  You have the sudden urge to make a blanket fort.  You indulge this urge, and are soon joined by the girls.
>Percy purrs quietly, gently running her hands across each blanket as she handles them.
>SO SOFT!
>You gently stroke her cap, then pat Pyr3's bony head.
>Both of them smile warmly, then pull you into a comfortable group hug.

[GET COMFY]

>The three of you settle down into your freshly-constructed fort, with Pyr3 adjusting her height as necessary.
>Percy purrs loudly and snuggles up against you.  She gently rubs her head against you, her cap gently squishing and deforming slightly.
