>And grabbing a handful of ass with the other arm.
>She once again winks lasciviously, and pulls you even closer.
>You soon feel a clawed hand slipping down towards your member...

>...once your very lengthy shower finally ends, you stagger out of the bathroom, fully dressed and satisfied.  Percy is sitting on the couch, reading.  She waves vaguely without looking up.
>Pyr3 whispers.
>"it's a g00d thing she's such a b00kw0rm, heh."

[RUN A BUBBLE BATH]

>You gently tap Percy on the shoulder, recoiling a bit when your hand meets one of her many mushrooms.
>She stops reading and looks over her shoulder at you.
>"Do you want to get cleaned up too?  I'll run you a bath."
>She nods appreciatively, so you head back to the bathroom.  Once there, you run a bubble bath.
>Not just a bubble bath: the sudsiest, bubbliest bath you've ever ran in your life.
>Only the best for your friend.
>Once it's all set, you go to grab her. She sets the e-reader down, and follows you, smiling warmly.
>Once you show off the bath, she laughs slowly, yet raucously.
>THAT'S A LOT OF BUBBLES
>"Yep; all for you."
>Suddenly, she dashes past you and leaps into the tub, sending soapy water everywhere.
>She resurfaces from the carpet of bubbles, cackling in her strange way.  She grins at you, then sinks into the water a bit, clearly relaxed.
>You gently rub her ears, and she purrs softly.  She soon lays back in the tub, basking in the warm, bubbly water.
>A smile slowly spreads across her face, and she reaches a hand out to gently pat you on the shoulder.

[CONTROL SHIFTING TO PERCY]

>Percy had never imagined that a tub could hold so many bubbles.
>It seemed that the suds towered over her head as she laid back. It gave her the impression of being in some grand canyon, nestled between soft, fragile mountains.
>She couldn't help but chuckle at the whimsical sight, though she was trying to regain her composure. A difficult task, given that she'd not experienced anything like this before.
>When they were in the lab, the scientists never did anything of this sort. If they felt she needed cleaning, they merely hosed her down from what they called a "safe distance."
>A small sigh escaped her throat as she dwelled on those days...
>Thankfully, the voice of Anon brought her out of her thoughts.
>"You want some help scrubbing?"
>She thought about it, and shook her head. She appreciated the offer, but wanted to just enjoy a nice soak.
>She sank further into the water, watching the various mushrooms coating her body gradually dip below the surface.
>Eventually there was little above water but her head and chest. She purred happily, enjoying the warmth and comfort of the bath water.